attributes.Long form description: The student tries to open the battery door, but it's stuck. They exchange the battery and try to take out the SD card, but it's also stuck. They exchange SD cards and turn on the GoPro, but it's not working. They turn it off and inspect it, then assemble it into the belt. They mount the strap onto the GoPro, but it's too loose. They disassemble the strap and assemble the handheld grip, but it's still not working.

attributes.Transcription: Please, change the battery of the GoPro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student attempts to open the battery door.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to open the battery door by pressing in the incorrect side.

attributes.Transcription: Push down on the bottom of the right side.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student presses the batterery door in the incorrect part.

attributes.Transcription: On the bottom of the right side of the GoPro, there should be a small thing that you can pull down.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to pull the battery door.

attributes.Transcription: You will have to pull it down from the right side, not from the bottom.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student pulls the mount instead of pull the battery door.
The student rotates the camera to a wrong position to open the battery door.
The student presses the incorrect side of the battery door.

attributes.Transcription: So, it's at the bottom of the right side.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student pulls the battery door without unlocking it.

attributes.Transcription: Pull the thing down that you tried a second ago, and then put it sideways.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student continue pressing the battery door to open it.

attributes.Transcription: And then, just open it sideways.
Ah!

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student did not insert correctly the battery door.
The student tries to close the battery door but it is not correctly inserted.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done.
Now, please also change the micro SD card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the SD card.

attributes.Transcription: It's at the same place as the battery.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to remove the SD card by pulling it.

attributes.Transcription: If you push on it, it should basically bounce out.
Mmm.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the new SD card.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done.
Now, please turn on the GoPro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on their GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: Good job!
Now, please turn it off again.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student presses the left button quickly,

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: Nicely done.
Now please attach the strap to the GoPro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inspects the GoPro and the belt.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student closes the mount of the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: Extend the two holes at the bottom of the GoPro, and then unscrew the screw from the strap.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the GoPro into the belt.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts the lock screw into the GoPro.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts the belt into the final part of the lock screw that is in the GoPRO.

attributes.Transcription: Take out the screw again and make sure that two holes from the GoPro are inside the two slots of the strap.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to insert the belt without removing the lock screw from the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: So take out the screw first.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the strap onto the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: And then put the GoPro into the two slots.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts one part of the mount into the belt.
The student tries to insert the lock screw into the mount.
The student rotates the lock screw by grabbing it in the incorrect part.

attributes.Transcription: Nicely done.
Now change from the strap to the handheld grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the strap from the GoPro.
The student assembles the handheld grip with the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done.
Now, please remove the handheld grip again.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the handheld grip from the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: Well done.
You can stop the recording now.
